    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a family of African birds comprising 7-10 species of fowl having a long neck with a hackle of long lance-shaped feathers, striped black, white, and blue, and a vulture-like bare blue head. In some classifications, they are placed in the pheasant family.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
